#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:12
msgid "Brush panel."
msgstr "Panneau Brush."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:14
msgid ""
"Painting needs paint brushes and Blender provides a Brush Panel within the "
"Tool Shelf when it operates in *Weight Paint Mode*."
msgstr ""
"La peinture nécessite des brosses de peinture et Blender fournit un panneau "
"*Brush* dans le *Tool Shelf* quand il opère en *Mode Weight Paint*."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:18
msgid ""
"In the :ref:`Data-Block menu <ui-data-block>` you find predefined Brush "
"Presets. And you can create your own custom presets as needed."
msgstr ""
"Dans le :ref:`menu Data-Block <ui-data-block>` vous trouverez des "
"préréglages de brosse prédéfinis. Et vous pouvez créer vos propres "
"préréglages personnalisés au besoin."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:25
msgid "Weight :kbd:`W`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:21
msgid ""
"The weight (color) to be used by the brush. However, the weight value is "
"applied to the Vertex Group in different ways depending on the selected "
"Brush Blending mode (see below)."
msgstr ""
"Le poids (couleur) à utiliser par la brosse. Cependant, la valeur de poids "
"est appliquée au groupe de sommets de différentes manières selon le mode "
"*Brush Blending* sélectionné (voir ci-dessous)."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:25
msgid ""
"Use :kbd:`Ctrl-LMB` to sample the weight value of clicked vertex. :kbd:"
"`Shift-LMB` lets you select the group from which to sample from."
msgstr ""
"Utilisez :kbd:`Ctrl-LMB` pour échantillonner la valeur de poids du sommet "
"cliqué. :kbd:`Maj-LMB` vous permet de sélectionner le groupe à partir duquel "
"échantillonner."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:27
msgid "Radius"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:28
msgid "The radius defines the area of influence of the brush."
msgstr "Le rayon définit la zone d'influence de la brosse."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:30
msgid "Strength"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:30
msgid ""
"This is the amount of paint to be applied per brush stroke. What that means "
"exactly also depends on the Brush Blending mode."
msgstr ""
"C'est la quantité de peinture à appliquer par coup de brosse. Ce que cela "
"signifie exactement dépend aussi du mode *Brush Blending*."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:67
msgid "Blend"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:33
msgid ""
"The brush :term:`Blend Modes` defines in which way the weight value is "
"applied to the Vertex Group while painting. In addition, here you can select "
"the *Blur* or *Smear* mode."
msgstr ""
"Les :term:`Blend Modes` de la brosse définissent la manière dont la valeur "
"de poids est appliquée au Groupe de sommets pendant la peinture. De plus, "
"ici vous pouvez sélectionner le mode *Blur* oo *Smear*."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:42
msgid "Mix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:39
msgid ""
"In this Blending mode the Weight value defines the *target weight* that will "
"eventually be reached when you paint long enough on the same location of the "
"mesh. And the strength determines how many strokes you need to place at the "
"target weight. Note that for strength = 1.0 the target weight is painted "
"immediately and for Weight = 0.0 the brush just does nothing."
msgstr ""
"Dans ce *Blending mode* la valeur *Weight (poids)* définit le *poids de la "
"cible* qui sera effectivement atteinte quand vous peignez assez longtemps à "
"la même place du maillage. Et la force détermine le nombre de traits "
"nécessaires à placer au poids de la cible. Notez que pour strength = 1.0e "
"poids de la cible est peint immédiatement et pour Weight = 0.0 la brosse ne "
"fait simplement rien."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:46
msgid "Add"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:45
msgid ""
"In this Blending mode the specified weight value is *added* to the vertex "
"weights. The strength determines which fraction of the weight gets added per "
"stroke. However, the brush will not paint weight values above 1.0."
msgstr ""
"Dans ce *Blending mode* la valeur de poids spécifiée est *ajoutée* aux poids "
"des sommets. La force (*strength*) détermine la fraction du poids à ajouter "
"par trait. Cependant, la brosse ne peindra pas les valeurs de poids au "
"dessus de 1.0."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:50
msgid "Subtract"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:49
msgid ""
"In this Blending mode the specified weight value is *subtracted* from the "
"vertex weights. The strength determines which fraction of the weight gets "
"removed per stroke. However, the brush will not paint weight values below "
"0.0."
msgstr ""
"Dans ce *Blending mode* la valeur de poids spécifiée est *soustraite* aux "
"poids des sommets. La force (*strength*) détermine la fraction du poids à "
"supprimer par trait. Cependant, la brosse ne peindra pas les valeurs de "
"poids au dessous de 0.0."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:55
msgid "Lighten"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:53
msgid ""
"In this Blending mode the specified weight value is interpreted as the "
"target weight. Very similar to the Mix Blending mode, but only weights below "
"the target weight are affected. Weights above the target weight remain "
"unchanged."
msgstr ""
"Dans ce *Blending mode* la valeur de poids spécifiée est interprétée comme "
"le poids cible. Très similaire au *Blending mode* Mix, Mais seules les poids "
"inférieurs au poids cible sont affectés. Les poids supérieurs au poids cible "
"restent inchangés. "

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:59
msgid "Darken"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:58
msgid ""
"This Blending mode is very similar to the Lighten Blending mode. But only "
"weights above the target weight are affected. Weights below the target "
"weight remain unchanged."
msgstr ""
"Ce *Blending mode* est très similaire au *Blending mode* Lighten. Mais "
"seules les poids supérieurs au poids de la cible sont affectés. Les poids "
"inférieurs au poids de la cible restent inchangés. "

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:62
msgid "Multiply"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:62
msgid ""
"Multiplies the vertex weights with the specified weight value. This is "
"somewhat like subtract, but the amount of removed weight is now dependent on "
"the Weight value itself."
msgstr ""
"Multiplie les poids des sommets par la valeur de poids spécifiée. C'est en "
"quelque sorte une soustraction, mais la quantité de poids supprimée est "
"maintenant dépendante de la valeur de poids elle-même."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:66
msgid "Blur"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:65
msgid ""
"Smooths out the weighting of adjacent vertices. In this mode the Weight "
"Value is ignored. The strength defines how much the smoothing is applied."
msgstr ""
"Lisse le poids des sommets adjacents. Dans ce mode la valeur de poids est "
"ignorée. La force définit le niveau de lissage appliqué."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:69
msgid "Accumulate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:70
msgid ""
"This will allow a stroke to accumulate on itself, just like an airbrush "
"would do."
msgstr ""
"Ceci va permettre à un trait de s'accumuler sur lui-même, tout comme un "
"airbrush le ferait."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:71
msgid "Front Faces Only"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:72
msgid "Only paint on the front side of faces."
msgstr "Peindre seulement sur la face avant des faces."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:76
msgid "Falloff Angle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:74
msgid ""
"As faces point away from the view the brush strokes fade away to prevent "
"harsh edges."
msgstr ""
"Plus les faces pointent loin de la vue, plus les traits de brosse "
"s'estompent pour éviter des bords dures."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:76
msgid "Angle"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:77
msgid "The angle at which the falloff begins."
msgstr "L'angle à partir duquel le falloff commence."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:79
msgid "2D Falloff"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:79
msgid ""
"This turns the brush influence into a cylinder (the depth along the view is "
"ignored) instead of a sphere."
msgstr ""
"Ceci transforme l'influence de la brosse en un cylindre (la profondeur sur "
"la vue est ignorée) au lieu d'une sphère."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:88
msgid "Auto Normalize"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:82
msgid ""
"Ensures that all deforming vertex groups add up to one while painting. When "
"this option is turned off, then all weights of a vertex can have any value "
"between 0.0 and 1.0. However, when Vertex Groups are used as Deform Groups "
"for character animation then Blender always interprets the weight values "
"relative to each other. That is, Blender always does a normalization over "
"all deform bones. Hence in practice it is not necessary to maintain a strict "
"normalization and further normalizing weights should not affect animation at "
"all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:88
msgid ""
"This option works most intuitively when used to maintain normalization while "
"painting on top of weights that are already normalized with some other tool."
msgstr ""
"Cette option fonctionne très intuitivement quand elle est utilisée pour "
"maintenir la normalisation pendant la peinture sur les poids qui sont déjà "
"normalisés avec un autre outil."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:115
msgid "Multi-Paint"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:91
msgid ""
"Paint on all selected Vertex Groups simultaneously, in a way that preserves "
"their relative influence. This can be useful when tweaking weights in an "
"area that is affected by more than three bones at once, e.g. certain areas "
"on a character's face."
msgstr ""
"Peint simultanément sur tous les groupes de sommets, d'une manière qui "
"préserve leur influence relative. Ceci peut être utile dans l'ajustement des "
"poids dans une zone qui est affectée par plus de trois *bones* à la fois, "
"ex. certaines zones du visage d'un personnage."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:95
msgid ""
"This option is only useful in the Armature tab, where you can select "
"multiple Vertex Groups by selecting multiple Pose bones. Once at least two "
"Vertex Groups are selected, viewport colors and paint logic switch to Multi-"
"Paint Mode, using the sum of the selected groups' weights if Auto Normalize "
"is enabled, and the average otherwise. Any paint operations aimed at this "
"collective weight are applied to individual Vertex Group weights in such way "
"that their ratio stays the same."
msgstr ""
"Cette option est seulement utile dans l'onglet *Armature*, où vous pouvez "
"sélectionner plusieurs groupes de sommets en sélectionnant plusieurs *Pose "
"bones*. Une fois qu'au moins deux groupes de sommets sont sélectionnés, les "
"couleurs de la vue et la logique de peinture changent en *Multi-Paint Mode*, "
"en utilisant la somme des poids des groupes sélectionnés si *Auto Normalize* "
"est activé, et la moyenne autrement. Toutes les opérations de peinture "
"visant ce poids collectif sont appliquées aux poids individuels des groupes "
"de sommets de telle manière que leur rapport reste le même."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:101
msgid ""
"Since the ratio is undefined if all weights are zero, Multi-Paint cannot "
"operate on vertices that do not have any weight assigned to the relevant "
"Vertex Groups. For this reason it also does not allow reducing the weight "
"all the way to zero. When used with X Mirror, it only guarantees completely "
"a symmetrical result if weights are initially symmetrical."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:108
msgid ""
"While Multi-Paint cannot directly paint on zero-weight vertices, it is "
"possible to use the *Smooth Weight* tool to copy a reasonable non-zero "
"weight distribution from adjacent vertices without leaving Multi-Paint Mode "
"or changing bone selection."
msgstr ""
"Alors que *Multi-Paint* ne peut pas directement peindre sur les sommets de "
"poids nul, il est possible d'utiliser l'outil *Smooth Weight* pour copier "
"une distribution de poids non nul acceptable à partir de sommets adjacents "
"sans quitter le *Multi-Paint Mode* ou changer de sélection d'os."

#: ../../manual/sculpt_paint/painting/weight_paint/tools.rst:112
msgid ""
"To do that, enable vertex selection, select target vertices, and apply one "
"iteration of the tool using vertex groups from *Selected Pose Bones* with "
"low Factor. After that simply paint on top to set the desired collective "
"weight."
msgstr ""
"Pour ce faire, activez la sélection de sommet, sélectionnez les sommets "
"cibles, et appliquez une itération de l'outil utilisant les groupes de "
"sommets de *Selected Pose Bones* avec un facteur bas. Après cela, peignez "
"simplement dessus pour fixer le poids collectif désiré."

